$ Excel: Home -> Editing -> Clear

Remove a cell's or range's content, its formatting, comments, hyperlinks or simply everything.

Functionality offered in the *Clear* drop down of the *Editing* section of the *Home* tab:
table { ll
   ☰ Equivalent command in → Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor/Immediate-Window
   Clear All ☰ `selection.clear`
   Clear Formats ☰ `selection.→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/clearFormats[clearFormats]`
   Clear Contents ☰ `selection.clearContents`
   Clear Comments and Notes ☰ `selection.clearComments`
   Clear Hyperlinks ☰ `selection.clearHyperlinks`
   Remove Hyperlinks ☰
table }

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/clear_[The `clear*` methods] of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[`range` object].

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/popups-and-dialogs/Format-Cells[Popup Menu *Format Cells*]
